        <?php echo $this->stencil->setHeadline('HTC - HTML Components'); ?>
        <p><strong>HTML Components (HTCs)</strong> are a legacy technology used to implement components in script as Dynamic HTML (<?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('DHTML', 'WD'); ?>) "behaviours" in the <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Microsoft Internet Explorer', 'WB'); ?> web browser. Such files typically use an <code>.htc</code> extension and the "<code>text/x-component</code>" <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('MIME type', 'WD'); ?>.</p>
        <p>An HTC is typically an <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('HTML', 'WD'); ?> file (with <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('JScript', 'JS'); ?> / <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('VBScript', 'L'); ?>) and a set of elements that define the component. This helps to organize behaviour encapsulated in script modules that can be attached to parts of a Webpage DOM.</p>
